// TerminalTabBar
// Drag-and-drop sortable tab bar for managing terminal sessions.
// Tabs can be selected, closed, renamed (double-click), and reordered via
// drag-and-drop using @dnd-kit. Only one tab is expanded for editing at a time.

FUNCTION SortableTab(tab, isActive, canClose, onSelect, onClose, onRename) -> JSX
  Uses useSortable hook (dnd-kit) for drag handle and transform styles.
  Active tab has blue underline; inactive tabs are gray.
  Double-clicking the name enters inline edit mode.
  Edit commits on Enter or blur; cancels on Escape.

---

FUNCTION handleDoubleClick() -> void
  Sets isEditing to true, pre-fills editValue with current tab name.

---

FUNCTION handleRename() -> void
  Trims editValue. IF non-empty, calls onRename(trimmed). Exits edit mode.

---

FUNCTION handleKeyDown(e) -> void
  Enter commits rename; Escape cancels and exits edit mode.

---

FUNCTION handleInputBlur() -> void
  Commits rename (calls handleRename).

---

FUNCTION TerminalTabBar(tabs, activeTabId, onTabSelect, onTabClose, onTabRename, onTabAdd, onTabReorder) -> JSX  EXPORT
  Wraps tabs in DndContext (closestCenter, pointer+keyboard sensors) and
  SortableContext (horizontalListSortingStrategy).
  Renders a SortableTab for each tab, plus a "+" button to add a new tab.

---

FUNCTION handleDragEnd(event) -> void
  Finds the old and new index of the dragged tab.
  IF indices are valid and different, calls onTabReorder(oldIndex, newIndex).
